Journal
 
When I came to this town it was for the promise of the boundless mineral wealth the recruiter boasted of. I'm glad they made no attempt to dress the place up as anything other than a hole-in-the-wall.
We've been working a good vein of magnetite for several weeks now, but iron isn't going for much these days, and after it's gone theres not much else to do.
Sinking a new tunnel, the night crew stumbled onto some vast cavern filled with water. Pure, clean water.
It's worth a hell of a lot more than iron, but the foreman says we're not to pump it out until we investigate the strange ruins at the lakes center.